      <t:profileDesc xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">
         <t:abstract>
            <t:p>The so-called "Ḫāylu Compilation" is a compilation of chronicles and other historiographic works begun by <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS5222haylaMi">Ḫāyla Mikāʾel ʾƎšate</t:persName> by collecting manuscripts and commissioning copies after
               a fire at the Royal Palace in <t:placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC3577Gondar">Gondar</t:placeName> destroyed many manuscripts. 
               The actual 'Ḫāylu Compilation' was produced during a later exile in <t:placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC4432Mahdar">Maḫdara Māryām</t:placeName> by
               <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS5222haylaMi">Ḫāyla Mikāʾel ʾƎšate</t:persName>'s friend and secretary <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS1007Abagaz">ʾAbagāz</t:persName>. After ending his compilatory work with the time of the exile in
               <t:placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC4432Mahdar">Maḫdara Māryām</t:placeName>, <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS1007Abagaz">ʾAbagāz</t:persName> continued by writing himself the history of <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS5222haylaMi">Ḫāyla Mikāʾel ʾƎšate</t:persName> and of Ethiopia,
               stopping after the death of <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS5222haylaMi">Ḫāyla Mikāʾel ʾƎšate</t:persName> in <t:date>1809</t:date>, which is not included in the Compilation.
            Some manuscripts contain brief accounts of events taking place after <t:date>1809</t:date>, but these do not form part of the original Compilation.
               Most of the works included in the Ḫāylu Compilation also circulate independently.</t:p>
         </t:abstract>
